data.title: Mitt Romney, Senator for Utah
data.meta_description: Legislative profile for Sen. Mitt Romney [R-UT], the  Senator from Utah
data.text:
Enacted Legislation

Romney was the primary sponsor of 5 bills that were enacted:

S. 308: Ending China’s Developing Nation Status Act

S. 1222 (117th): Bonneville Shoreline Trail Advancement Act

S. 3588 (117th): Medical Countermeasures Surge Capacity Act of 2022

S. 2150 (117th): Wildland Fire Mitigation and Management Commission Act of 2021

S. 1207 (116th): Navajo Utah Water Rights Settlement Act of 2019

View All »

Does 5 not sound like a lot? Very few bills are ever enacted — most legislators sponsor only a handful that are signed into law. But there are other legislative activities that we don’t track that are also important, including offering amendments, committee work and oversight of the other branches, and constituent services.
